project.title: GEOTECHNICAL INVESTIGATION AT PUERTO RICO ELECTRIC POWER AUTHORITY SITES

stratigraphy.title: Fill
stratigraphy.description: clayey GRAVEL (GC), mostly fine to coarse, hard, subangular, limestone gravel, some clay, few fine- to medium-grained, moist, reddish-brown

stratigraphy.title: Soft organic soil
stratigraphy.description: lean CLAY (CL), soft, medium plasticity, organic, moist, dark gray to black

stratigraphy.title: Alluvium
stratigraphy.description: fat CLAY (CH), mostly high plasticity, stiff to very hard, trace fine-grained sand, moist, mottled red, yellow, and light gray
sandy fat CLAY (CH), mostly high plasticity, hard, some fine- to medium-grained sand, trace round fine hard gravel, moist, reddish brown
clayey SAND (SC), soft to medium, mostly fine- to medium-grained sand, some clay, moist, tan to yellowish brown

stratigraphy.title: Highly weathered limestone
stratigraphy.description: clayey GRAVEL (GC), fine, angular, weathered to hard limestone fragments (broken by sampler), some pockets of clay, some fine- to medium-grained sand, wet, tan to pale yellow
